":"Zweden","Sverige":"Zweden"},"en":{"–after 1321":"–after 1321","–1321":"–1321","–Female":"Deceased","1300–1350":"1300–1350","1307–Female":"1307–Deceased","1320–1390":"1320–1390","–Male":"Deceased","–1299":"–1299","16 May 1306":"16 May 1306","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","abt 1320":"about 1320","1390":"1390","omkring 1307":"about 1307","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1266":"1266","1321":"1321","1320":"1320","after 1321":"after 1321","1318":"1318","1307":"1307","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Sweden","Sverige":"Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nilsson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Lars, Nils, Per, Anders, Egil, Lennart, Sven, Birgit, Fredrik, Sten, Algot.  German Kurt, Hans, Otto, Gerhard, Gotthard, Karl-Heinz.","Swedish and German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Nils</i>, a shortened form of <i>Nikolaus</i>. Compare   Nilson  ,   Neilson   3, and   Nielson   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Nilson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Nils, Erik, Alvar, Holger, Kristoffer, Mats, Sven.","Americanized form (and a rare Swedish variant) of Swedish   Nilsson  .","Americanized form of Norwegian   Nilsen   and of Danish, Norwegian, or North German   Nielsen  , all cognates of 1. Compare   Nielson  ."]}]},{"name":"Bo","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and Danish: originally a byname for a householder, derived from Old Norse <i>búa</i> ‘to dwell, have a household’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357046,"age":46,"year":"1250","julianDay":2177614,"description":"King Eriksson died. Valdemar crowned King. Birger Jarl declared regent until Valdemar is of age.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1702074,"age":48,"year":"1252","julianDay":2178344,"title":"Earliest Mention of Stockholm","description":"The earliest known recorded history of the city of Stockholm is in Norse sagas as Agnafit which dates to 1252. The city rose to prominence due to Baltic trade. Stockholm is now the most populous urban area in the region.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357047,"age":62,"year":"1266","julianDay":2183458,"description":"King Valdemar overthrown by brothers.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1702075,"age":102,"year":"1306","julianDay":2198067,"title":"The Hatuna Games","description":"A conflict on September 29, 1306, between Birger, King of Sweden, and his brothers, the dukes Eric Magnusson and Valdemar Magnusson is known as The Hatuna Games. The brothers arrived to a party late in the night at King Birger's estate. The dukes captured and imprisoned Birger and his wife in Nykoping Castle's dungeon. Duke Eric then gained power over Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357048,"age":114,"year":"1318","julianDay":2202450,"description":"Peasants revolted against King.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Bo Nilsson Natt och Dag was born as the son of Nils Sigridsson Natt och Dag and Mrs. Nils Sigridsson. He married Cecilia Knutsdotter Aspenäs on 16 May 1306. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 3 daughters. He died after 1321, in Sweden."},"et":{"–after 1321":"–pärast 1321","–1321":"–1321","–Female":"Surnud","1300–1350":"1300–1350","1307–Female":"1307–Surnud","1320–1390":"1320–1390","–Male":"Surnud","–1299":"–1299","16 May 1306":"16. mai 1306","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1390":"1390","omkring 1307":"umbes 1307","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1266":"1266","1321":"1321","1320":"1320","after 1321":"pärast 1321","1318":"1318","1307":"1307","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Rootsi","Sverige":"Rootsi"},"fi":{"–after 1321":"–1321 jälkeen","–1321":"–1321","–Female":"Kuollut","1300–1350":"1300–1350","1307–Female":"1307–Kuollut","1320–1390":"1320–1390","–Male":"Kuollut","–1299":"–1299","16 May 1306":"16. toukokuuta 1306","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","abt 1320":"noin 1320","1390"